{"key":"processedPost-15945324","value":{"id":15945324,"first":15945231,"last":15945706,"when":1331733180,"utime":"03/14/12 04:53 PM","cleanedPost":"Doing a white balance on perlite in a terrarium in bright daylight is essentially how I came up with the figure of 5000K to 7000K as being optimum for mushroom growing, after noticing that mushrooms grew much better when a terrarium was set outdoors in sunlight for several minutes per day.&nbsp; You can use your naked eye though.&nbsp; The perlite should be white, but with an almost imperceptible blue tint.&nbsp; Of course, these days our lamps are labeled in color temperature so it's much easier on us.<br />Of course, if you're growing outdoors it's like taking a fat girl to the prom.&nbsp; You dance with what you brought.<br />RR"}}